  "case": "runtime_cyclone_nonlinear_miller",
  "claim_scope": "Mapped velocity-basis readiness for cached linear RHS assembly. Timings are single-state JAX warm-call measurements; gamma/omega values are Rayleigh-quotient proxies unless dense eigen fields are populated. The eigen_scorecard field adds a tiny actual assembled-RHS dense operator check for mapped identity consistency. The krylov_scorecard field additionally runs the mapped operator through the production Krylov eigen wrapper on the same compact grid and compares Krylov eigenvalues with the nearest dense eigenvalues, then validates returned-vector residuals against that same materialized operator. Nonlinear real-space mapped-basis support is not asserted here, and any input nonlinear term is forced off for this benchmark.",
